headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 24 points in three quarters and the Orlando Magic beat the Sacramento Kings 121-91 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paolo Banchero scores 24 points in 3 quarters in the Magic's 121-91 victory over the Kings

headlines.description: — Drew Timme scored the go-ahead basket on a cutting layup with 7.7 seconds left and the Brooklyn Nets beat the NBA-worst Washington Wizards 115-112 on Saturday night to end a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Drew Timme scores go-ahead basket in the Nets' 115-112 victory over the NBA-worst Wizards

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 30 points to lead the Miami Heat to a 118-95 victory over the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro scores 30 points to lead Heat to 4th straight win with 118-95 victory over eliminated 76ers

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson scored 20 points, P.J. Washington had 19 and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Chicago Bulls 120-119 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavericks outlast Bulls 120-119 to pad lead in play-in race

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Austin Reaves had 31 points and eight assists, Luka Doncic added 29 points and nine assists and the Los Angeles Lakers held on for a 134-127 win over Memphis on Saturday night in the Grizzlies' first game under interim coach Tuomas Iisalo.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reaves, Doncic lead Lakers to 134-127 victory over Grizzlies, spoiling Iisalo's debut

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 33 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder routed the Indiana Pacers 132-111 on Saturday night for their ninth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 33 as league-leading Thunder top Pacers 132-111 for 9th straight win

events.name: Boston Celtics at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 29 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists and the Boston Celtics won their eighth straight, beating the San Antonio Spurs 121-111 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum's 29 points, 10 rebounds powers Celtics past Spurs for eighth straight victory, 121-111
